00:34:01.200 --> 00:34:08.079
layers. Uh there are lots of techniques

00:34:05.039 --> 00:34:12.639
uh that are devised to deal with this

00:34:08.079 --> 00:34:16.800
issue. uh some uh that are more common

00:34:12.639 --> 00:34:18.560
we will discuss in this lecture but of

00:34:16.800 --> 00:34:20.480
course there are other techniques that

00:34:18.560 --> 00:34:22.079
can be tailored for different

00:34:20.480 --> 00:34:23.599
architectures.

00:34:22.079 --> 00:34:25.520
So

00:34:23.599 --> 00:34:27.280
we will start with a very common

00:34:25.520 --> 00:34:29.679
technique that is uh considered

00:34:27.280 --> 00:34:32.159
foundational when we are dealing with

00:34:29.679 --> 00:34:35.599
the mini batch uh training and the mini

00:34:32.159 --> 00:34:40.320
batch is rather not small and it's it

00:34:35.599 --> 00:34:43.119
can be reliably large and uh we can use

00:34:40.320 --> 00:34:44.720
a batch normalization. So bash

00:34:43.119 --> 00:34:46.800
normalization

00:34:44.720 --> 00:34:49.679
is basically

00:34:46.800 --> 00:34:52.879
u a way to normalize the pre-activation

00:34:49.679 --> 00:34:56.240
values in the network.

00:34:52.879 --> 00:35:01.119
So it is inserted at

00:34:56.240 --> 00:35:03.760
u uh before the linear layers and before

00:35:01.119 --> 00:35:06.640
the nonlinear activation functions.

00:35:03.760 --> 00:35:08.880
Hence the they are getting the value z.

00:35:06.640 --> 00:35:11.359
And how it works is basically for each

00:35:08.880 --> 00:35:14.160
mini batch during training batch

00:35:11.359 --> 00:35:16.560
normalization first calculates the mean

00:35:14.160 --> 00:35:20.480
and variance of these pre-activation

00:35:16.560 --> 00:35:23.200
values the Z's and then normalizes them

00:35:20.480 --> 00:35:26.560
to have a mean zero and a variance of

00:35:23.200 --> 00:35:32.160
one. The normalized Z can be written

00:35:26.560 --> 00:35:36.480
this way where mu b is the mean and

00:35:32.160 --> 00:35:40.079
sigma 2 uh b is the variance of the

00:35:36.480 --> 00:35:42.960
current mini batch b.

00:35:40.079 --> 00:35:45.200
So epsilon is a is a constant just for

00:35:42.960 --> 00:35:49.200
numerical stability.

00:35:45.200 --> 00:35:51.760
Uh this basically gives us um

00:35:49.200 --> 00:35:55.359
somehow counterintuitive

00:35:51.760 --> 00:35:58.880
uh uh point meaning that we are

00:35:55.359 --> 00:36:02.079
introducing new parameters, right? And

00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:04.079
why we should force the signal to be a

00:36:02.079 --> 00:36:07.359
standard normal

00:36:04.079 --> 00:36:10.240
only to immediately change it and the

00:36:07.359 --> 00:36:13.359
reason is a standard normal distribution

00:36:10.240 --> 00:36:15.920
may not be optimal for the next layer.

00:36:13.359 --> 00:36:18.560
So forcing all activations into this

00:36:15.920 --> 00:36:22.400
rigid structure might limit the

00:36:18.560 --> 00:36:26.079
network's representation power. So how

00:36:22.400 --> 00:36:28.560
can we resolve that? To solve this, this

00:36:26.079 --> 00:36:33.200
uh batch normalization layer basically

00:36:28.560 --> 00:36:40.040
learns two new parameters. A scale

00:36:33.200 --> 00:36:40.040
uh that we denote by gamma and a shifted

00:36:40.400 --> 00:36:47.359
by beta. So this parameters um gamma and

00:36:45.359 --> 00:36:49.280
beta

00:36:47.359 --> 00:36:54.800
basically

00:36:49.280 --> 00:36:58.079
shift and scale uh the z hat uh that we

00:36:54.800 --> 00:37:01.440
uh computed here

00:36:58.079 --> 00:37:04.480
and we are going to call it a bash norm

00:37:01.440 --> 00:37:07.280
output. So what does this mean?

00:37:04.480 --> 00:37:10.960
basically means that the network learns

00:37:07.280 --> 00:37:13.760
the ideal mean variance for the

00:37:10.960 --> 00:37:15.680
activation. So in the worst case when

00:37:13.760 --> 00:37:18.560
the original distribution was best the

00:37:15.680 --> 00:37:22.160
network can simply learn the uh to go to

00:37:18.560 --> 00:37:24.960
send the C uh hat to the previous point

00:37:22.160 --> 00:37:29.119
that it was.

00:37:24.960 --> 00:37:32.480
But this uh normalization method helped

00:37:29.119 --> 00:37:35.920
for a lot of uh good behavior during the

00:37:32.480 --> 00:37:38.320
training. It makes the optimization much

00:37:35.920 --> 00:37:40.400
smoother

00:37:38.320 --> 00:37:43.680
and the reason is because the last

00:37:40.400 --> 00:37:47.119
landscape will be smoother and the

00:37:43.680 --> 00:37:48.880
optimizer can converge more reliably. In

00:37:47.119 --> 00:37:51.280
that case

00:37:48.880 --> 00:37:54.240
the learning rates can be chosen to be

00:37:51.280 --> 00:37:57.599
higher which means that the training can

00:37:54.240 --> 00:38:01.200
be faster significantly faster in a lot

00:37:57.599 --> 00:38:04.560
of cases. And uh on the other hand this

00:38:01.200 --> 00:38:07.520
basically has a regularization effect.

00:38:04.560 --> 00:38:10.640
The noise the noise that we introduce

00:38:07.520 --> 00:38:14.400
with this mini batch statistics

00:38:10.640 --> 00:38:17.760
u has some regularization effect and uh

00:38:14.400 --> 00:38:20.320
it helps to reduce the need for uh

00:38:17.760 --> 00:38:22.640
techniques other techniques that uh does

00:38:20.320 --> 00:38:26.560
the same regularization like dropouts

00:38:22.640 --> 00:38:31.280
that you will see later also this u

00:38:26.560 --> 00:38:34.400
batch normalization um uh even make the

00:38:31.280 --> 00:38:39.359
dependence on the initial initial weight

00:38:34.400 --> 00:38:42.560
choice even uh less and uh this

00:38:39.359 --> 00:38:44.240
basically um

00:38:42.560 --> 00:38:47.200
um even if your choice of the

00:38:44.240 --> 00:38:48.800
initialization was not the best uh

00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:52.320
during the training the batch

00:38:48.800 --> 00:38:56.000
normalization will will somehow help to

00:38:52.320 --> 00:38:58.160
to fix that uh issue.

00:38:56.000 --> 00:39:00.800
So uh even with all of these

00:38:58.160 --> 00:39:03.760
normalization techniques

00:39:00.800 --> 00:39:07.040
uh as you will see during the course uh

00:39:03.760 --> 00:39:10.400
when we train very deep networks this

00:39:07.040 --> 00:39:13.680
issue of um vanishing gradients will

00:39:10.400 --> 00:39:16.480
eventually uh come at us especially if

00:39:13.680 --> 00:39:20.320
we want to go very deep uh training very

00:39:16.480 --> 00:39:23.839
deep neural networks. So one way to

00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:25.599
resolve that al together is just to add

00:39:23.839 --> 00:39:30.480
connections

00:39:25.599 --> 00:39:34.320
uh that basically passes the the layers

00:39:30.480 --> 00:39:38.079
and this way we basically provide the

00:39:34.320 --> 00:39:42.000
the signal from the before the layer to

00:39:38.079 --> 00:39:44.640
the after the layer. And uh this way it

00:39:42.000 --> 00:39:48.400
it's like not just a highway. It's a

00:39:44.640 --> 00:39:52.640
super highway basically. Uh that give us

00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:56.320
um uh that allows the input of a block

00:39:52.640 --> 00:40:00.240
of layers let's say x here to be added

00:39:56.320 --> 00:40:03.520
directly to its output. Um so if fx here

00:40:00.240 --> 00:40:06.800
this is the the layer that um acts like

00:40:03.520 --> 00:40:09.520
a function fx and then we have the

00:40:06.800 --> 00:40:11.440
output here will be

00:40:09.520 --> 00:40:16.720
fx

00:40:11.440 --> 00:40:20.880
plus x right and uh this basically

00:40:16.720 --> 00:40:23.359
is the an inter uninterrupted path for

00:40:20.880 --> 00:40:26.560
the gradients especially to flow

00:40:23.359 --> 00:40:29.200
through. Even if a particular block of

00:40:26.560 --> 00:40:32.000
layer uh like for example here in this

00:40:29.200 --> 00:40:34.880
case is not useful the network can

00:40:32.000 --> 00:40:37.920
easily learn to make uh its output fx

00:40:34.880 --> 00:40:40.800
close to zero right and it's basically

00:40:37.920 --> 00:40:43.520
bypass that layer altogether and the

00:40:40.800 --> 00:40:46.960
gradient flows backward through the

00:40:43.520 --> 00:40:49.760
identity connection uh without any de

00:40:46.960 --> 00:40:52.240
diminish in the value.

00:40:49.760 --> 00:40:54.880
This uh was the innovation in the

00:40:52.240 --> 00:40:56.400
residual network or in short ResNet

00:40:54.880 --> 00:40:59.200
architectures

00:40:56.400 --> 00:41:01.839
that allows for training very deep

00:40:59.200 --> 00:41:04.880
neural networks. One thing that we

00:41:01.839 --> 00:41:09.359
should be careful uh when we we want to

00:41:04.880 --> 00:41:13.040
use this u technique is to make sure the

00:41:09.359 --> 00:41:16.720
output of the layer and the input has

00:41:13.040 --> 00:41:21.040
the same shape. Otherwise we cannot use

00:41:16.720 --> 00:41:23.359
this uh technique. Another thing is uh

00:41:21.040 --> 00:41:26.640
this is designed for very deep neural

00:41:23.359 --> 00:41:29.520
networks. So for shallow uh networks

00:41:26.640 --> 00:41:32.800
this is not necessary and maybe even not

00:41:29.520 --> 00:41:36.240
helpful. So we conclude the lecture

00:41:32.800 --> 00:41:39.200
here. Uh but it doesn't mean that there

00:41:36.240 --> 00:41:42.000
are not other ways to make sure our

00:41:39.200 --> 00:41:44.800
training is not stable. And during the

00:41:42.000 --> 00:41:47.119
course you will see that uh we will

00:41:44.800 --> 00:41:49.520
choose multiple or combination of these

00:41:47.119 --> 00:41:52.880
techniques. And for different

00:41:49.520 --> 00:41:54.480
architectures we use different uh

00:41:52.880 --> 00:41:58.880
combinations.

00:41:54.480 --> 00:42:02.800
And uh these are uh this will be one of

00:41:58.880 --> 00:42:05.200
the uh tools in your disposal as a as an

00:42:02.800 --> 00:42:09.359
engineer who who does tradeoff for

00:42:05.200 --> 00:42:12.319
example in the design which one of this

00:42:09.359 --> 00:42:15.359
design for this specific architecture

00:42:12.319 --> 00:42:17.680
can give you the best result. And uh

00:42:15.359 --> 00:42:20.880
this will be one of the points that you

00:42:17.680 --> 00:42:23.920
have to even maybe try different

00:42:20.880 --> 00:42:25.920
techniques uh when you are training in

00:42:23.920 --> 00:42:29.359
neural network and at the end choose the

00:42:25.920 --> 00:42:29.359
one that give you the best soft.
